Again, alive2 shows that `%is_const` is always false because `%c` is not a compile-time constant. But the important point is that we shouldn't make assumptions about `llvm.is.constant` based on value equality.

Let me look at the actual implementation of the patch again. The key change is in `simplifyWithOpReplaced`:

```cpp
// Don't fold away llvm.is.constant checks based on assumptions.
if (match(I, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::is_constant>()))
  return nullptr;
```

This prevents `simplifyWithOpReplaced` from trying to simplify `llvm.is.constant` intrinsics when we're replacing operands based on equality assumptions.

